                            <comment id="13199703" author="gtully" created="Fri, 3 Feb 2012 13:47:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fix in: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1240162&amp;amp;view=rev&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc?rev=1240162&amp;amp;view=rev&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For new queues that match the virtual interceptor prefixes configured, an entry is added to the ack table and the get destinations query unions distinct on ack and messages table. This allows them to be found and loaded on start.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
